```
sudo apt-get install autogen autoconf libtool
```
when you want to autoreconf ,you should run `aclocal` first and parse `m4_include([macros.m4])` to 
the botton of aclocal.m4

```
m4_define([LT_PACKAGE_VERSION], [2.4.2])
m4_define([LT_PACKAGE_REVISION], [1.3337])

[macro_version='2.4.2'
macro_revision='1.3337'
```

run `autoconf -f&&automake -a`



